The Champions League round of 16 draw will be conducted on Monday. It will see a lot of big clashes, following the confirmation of seedings last week. Atletico Madrid, Borussia Dortmund, Chelsea, Real Madrid and Tottenham Hotspur all finished as runners-up in their group. They will all be drawn against one of the group winners: Barcelona, Bayern Munich, Juventus, Liverpool, Manchester City and Paris Saint-Germain. The draw will take place at 12noon West African time. The first legs will be played on February, 18, 19, 25 and 26, with group winners away from home. Second leg ties will be played on March 10, 11, 17 and 18. Group winners: Barcelona, Bayern Munich, Juventus, Liverpool, Manchester City, Paris Saint-Germain, RB Leipzig, Valencia Runners-up: Atalanta, Atletico Madrid, Borussia Dortmund, Chelsea, Lyon, Napoli, Real Madrid, Tottenham Hotspur Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.